# CODEOWNERS — Perxli
#
# This file determines who is automatically requested for review on PRs.
# Branch protection can enforce "require review from Code Owners" once real
# owners are listed here.
#
# Reference:
#   https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositories-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# Format:
#   <path-pattern>  @<github-username-or-team>
#
# Order matters — the LAST matching pattern wins.

# ── Catch-all ──
# Uncomment and set when there's a default reviewer for everything.
# *                              @your-github-handle

# ── Architecture and decisions ──
# /docs/decisions/               @your-tech-lead
# /AGENTS.md                     @your-tech-lead
# /CLAUDE.md                     @your-product-lead

# ── Backend ──
# /backend/                      @your-backend-lead
# /backend/src/integrations/     @your-backend-lead @your-security-lead

# ── Frontend ──
# /frontend/                     @your-frontend-lead

# ── Infrastructure ──
# /.github/                      @your-infra-lead
# /docker-compose*.yml           @your-infra-lead
# /backend/Dockerfile            @your-infra-lead
# /frontend/Dockerfile           @your-infra-lead

# ── Sensitive surfaces ──
# Payment and signing logic — extra scrutiny.
# /backend/src/services/payments.service.ts        @your-backend-lead @your-security-lead
# /backend/src/services/signing.service.ts         @your-backend-lead @your-security-lead
# /backend/src/integrations/mpesa/                 @your-backend-lead @your-security-lead

# ── Until a team is assigned ──
# Leave this file with only comments. Branch-protection "require review from
# Code Owners" is a no-op until at least one owner is matched by a pattern.
